main event: A yellowish, finned object was observed in Bettles, Alaska on February 8, 1953.
interesting points: The object was stationary at 00:000 ft, had a yellowish fin possibly caused by contracting metal, and had a light interior.
The object left a trail of billowing smoke about 5 miles long.
Attempts were made to measure the object's speed, which was estimated at 200 MPH.
The object then accelerated extremely rapidly and a needle-like object was seen sticking out in front.
No report is on file for this sighting.
